The Board will attempt to answer as many questions as possible during the meeting.

Please see below a link that will enable spectators to purchase tickets to our home football game on August 28th with Cannon County. Student tickets are $3 and adult tickets are $6. There will be a small service fee assessed for each ticket. The tickets are provided through GoFan, a digital ticketing vendor. Download the GoFan App from the App Store and purchase tickets. The service is secure and is used by high schools across the country. The ticket(s) will be sent directly to the purchaser's phone and can be redeemed at the gate. GoFan will provide the purchaser easy instructions on how to redeem tickets. This process will allow fans to skip the ticket line and enter Nunley Stadium directly after a temperature check. The total number of tickets available will be 850.

post_text:
From the Director of schools, Mr. Grant Swallows...

"I am responding to some misinformation related to the VIP@Home program. The application deadline passed on Tuesday, August 4. Due to the overwhelming response of students requesting this option, the district team met to discuss staffing needs. The number of students learning at home will lessen the number of students learning in the building. Because of that fact, we have reached out to schools to try and coordinate help in organizing how students will learn in VIP@Home. There has been no change to the curriculum offerings. From the beginning of this process, WCS knew that an expansion of learning at home would change the way the system operates. WCS is committed to educating all students in whatever environment they choose this year. When all of the details are finalized, more information will be made available. Students who requested the VIP@Home program should be receiving an email soon."

Pre K and Kindergarten screening will be held at Warren County High School gym Tuesday (June 9) 10 am to 6 pm, Wednesday (June 10) 8 am to 3 pm and Thursday (June 11) 10 am to 6 pm. Those registering for kindergarten may complete registration online or come to Warren County High School if needing assistance. If you are registering for Pre K you must complete paper registration at Warren County High School and bring proof of income, proof of address, and birth certificate. Children do not need to attend with parents.

If you have completed a new student registration online for a student in another grade level and still need to submit the required documents you are welcome to bring those documents to the high school gym during this screening.

This testing will be provided at no cost to participants, and those who come for testing can remain in their vehicles throughout the process of collecting their samples.

Due to cell phone spam filters please add Warren County Schools Central Office phone number(931-668-4022) to your cell phone contacts. You will also need to add the main phone number of the school(s) that your children attend. This will help to alleviate the blocking of our school notification calls.

I am also suggesting that all parents/guardians add their cell number to receive a text message in family access.
Directions:
Login to family access and click Skylert on the left side of your screen. Wait for that screen to load and type your cell phone number where it displays text message numbers at the bottom of that screen and save. Text messages are delivered much faster.

Thank you!

National Bullying Prevention Month
Every October, schools, and organizations across the country join STOMP Out Bullying™ in observing National Bullying Prevention Month. The goal is to encourage schools, communities, and organizations to work together to stop bullying and cyberbullying and increase awareness of the prevalence and impact of all forms of bullying on all children of all ages.

post_text:
The adverse weather of late Winter 2019 has detrimentally impacted our community through torrential rain, flash flooding and heavy winds causing many of our local businesses to limit their hours of operation and in most cases close temporarily. Our neighbors in business still incur expenses even when their doors are not open. The Chamber of Commerce and Warren County Government are encouraging our citizens to shop and eat locally as much as possible April 1st-7th or
“Shop & Eat Across Warren Co. Week”.

If you’ve been looking to add Spring/Summer items to your wardrobe, purchase a gift for a special someone, select a new piece of decor/furniture for your home, take the family out for dinner or service your vehicle, please make your choice locally and support those who help keep Warren County a wonderful place to live. Shopping and dining locally is always a great decision, especially when helping our neighbors recover what has been lost recently due to uncontrollable circumstances.

post_text: Saint Thomas Health is hosting a FREE Medical Mission at home at Warren County High School on Saturday, July 28th accepting patients from 8 am until 2pm. Medical care, dental care, vision, and select screenings and lab tests are offered to individuals free of charge. Local community agencies will also be on site to offer additional resources. Services are provided on a first come, first served basis at Warren County High School on Pioneer Lane in McMinnville. For more information, visit sthealth.com/medicalmission.

post_text:
Tip Line for Warren County Schools

In an effort to increase safety, the Warren County School District in conjunction with Warren County Sherriff’s Department has developed an anonymous TEXT-A-TIP line: 931-952-6770. We want to encourage anyone who has information regarding someone selling drugs, threatening to hurt others, having or planning to bring weapons on campus, as well as any illegal activity or public safety concerns in the schools, to text that information to the TEXT-A-TIP line. Any information regarding any school may be sent via text and will go directly to a school resource officer.

IF ANYONE HAS INFORMATION THAT IS AN EMERGENCY, THEY SHOULD CALL 911.

We feel this will be another avenue to help provide important information to authorities and help us all to stay safe.
